{"nodes": [{"id": "design_radio_sim", "label": "radio_sim (C process)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "design_bridge_py", "label": "bridge.py (Python bridge layer)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "design_mock_client_py", "label": "mock_client.py (Python mock client)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "design_mosquitto", "label": "Mosquitto (local MQTT broker)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "design_msg_queue", "label": "Bounded thread-safe message queue", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Needs a mutex plus two condition variables (not_empty, not_full), not just a mutex, so producer/consumer threads block correctly when the queue is empty/full; it is the one core primitive everything else in radio_sim builds on."}, {"id": "design_pubsub", "label": "Pub/sub layer (topic registry, fan-out)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Publishing clones the message into every subscriber's own queue rather than calling handlers directly, so one slow subscriber can never stall another."}, {"id": "design_worker_pool", "label": "Worker thread pool", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "design_transport_thread", "label": "Transport thread", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "design_command_listener", "label": "Command-listener thread", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "design_handshake", "label": "HELLO/HELLO_ACK/HELLO_NACK protocol version handshake", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Plain text, line-based, deliberately not JSON, to avoid a chicken-and-egg problem of needing to already agree on a format before agreeing on one. Connection-level negotiation fits a persistent Unix socket better than per-message versioning (used on connectionless transports like UDP), since there is a well-defined moment (connection setup) to agree on a version once."}, {"id": "design_client_conn_t", "label": "client_conn_t (per-connection state struct)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "design_version_1_schema", "label": "Schema version 1 (JSON telemetry/alert)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "design_version_2_schema", "label": "Schema version 2 (JSON telemetry, additive + breaking change)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Deliberately includes both kinds of schema change: the new temperature_c field is additive/backward-compatible (a v1-only client never sees it), while ts moving from a Unix epoch integer to an ISO-8601 string is a breaking change a v1 client would fail to parse -- exactly why the handshake matters."}, {"id": "design_protobuf_wire_format", "label": "Protobuf wire-format upgrade", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Build the JSON version first and swap the wire format to protobuf as its own deliberate later exercise, so migrating a working wire format can be practiced and compared directly against the JSON approach. Protobuf handles additive schema change for free via field numbers, but a real breaking change (like the ts type change) still isn't safe in place -- you'd retire the field number or lean on the connection-level handshake."}, {"id": "design_protobuf_c", "label": "protobuf-c toolchain", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "design_envelope_message", "label": "Envelope (protobuf message)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "design_telemetry_message", "label": "Telemetry (protobuf message)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "design_alert_message", "label": "Alert (protobuf message)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "design_length_prefix_framing", "label": "4-byte length-prefix framing", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Protobuf gives compact bytes but no built-in message boundaries on a stream socket; a 4-byte big-endian length prefix before each serialized Envelope is the standard fix, and both the C writer and Python reader must agree on it explicitly."}, {"id": "design_msg_pool", "label": "Pre-allocated fixed-size message pool", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Replaces malloc/free in the message hot path with acquire/release against a fixed-size, pre-allocated pool, avoiding unbounded allocator time and long-run heap fragmentation the way real embedded firmware does. Trade-off: pre-committed worst-case memory and a closed/size-capped set of message shapes (the pool must be sized to the largest of telemetry/alert payloads); not the default choice for a general-purpose backend service."}, {"id": "design_msg_pool_acquire", "label": "msg_pool_acquire()", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "design_msg_pool_release", "label": "msg_pool_release()", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "design_exhaustion_policy", "label": "Pool exhaustion policy", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "msg_pool_acquire returns NULL on exhaustion; the caller drops and logs/counts the message rather than blocking or falling back to malloc, matching msg_queue_try_enqueue's non-blocking drop-and-move-on precedent. A malloc fallback would quietly defeat the entire point of the pool."}, {"id": "design_sigint_shutdown", "label": "SIGINT clean shutdown", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A SIGINT handler signals all threads to stop, drains queues, and joins every thread before exiting -- worth building deliberately since 'how do you shut down a multithreaded system cleanly' is a very plausible question in its own right."}, {"id": "design_phase_1", "label": "Phase 1 -- foundational queue + pub/sub", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Stop here and it's already worth something: pthread_create, mutex/cond-var discipline, and pub/sub fan-out are all demonstrable from code that actually runs. Realistic minimum bar for the whole project."}, {"id": "design_phase_2", "label": "Phase 2 -- networking, handshake, shutdown", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "design_phase_3", "label": "Phase 3 -- bridge.py + Mosquitto", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "design_phase_4", "label": "Phase 4, stretch -- mock_client.py + tests", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "design_phase_5", "label": "Phase 5, stretch -- version 2 negotiation", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "design_phase_6", "label": "Phase 6, stretch -- protobuf wire-format swap", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "design_phase_7", "label": "Phase 7, stretch -- message pool hardening", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}], "edges": [{"source": "design_radio_sim", "target": "design_msg_queue", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "design_radio_sim", "target": "design_worker_pool", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "design_radio_sim", "target": "design_pubsub", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "design_radio_sim", "target": "design_transport_thread", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "design_radio_sim", "target": "design_command_listener", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "design_radio_sim", "target": "design_sigint_shutdown", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "design_worker_pool", "target": "design_pubsub", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "design_transport_thread", "target": "design_pubsub", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "DESIGN.md", "source_location":